Make your own spray with water, witch hazel, and a few drops of tea tree or lavender oil.

&nbsp;

These natural oils kill bacteria and leave gear smelling fresher without chemicals.

&nbsp;
<h1>19. Dryer Sheets in Cleats</h1>
This classic hack works wonders.

&nbsp;

Slip a dryer sheet into each cleat after practice, and the shoes will smell much better by game day.

&nbsp;
<h1>20. Sunlight Is Free</h1>
Don’t underestimate nature’s disinfectant.

&nbsp;

Leaving cleats and shin guards in direct sunlight helps kill bacteria and dries them out quickly.

&nbsp;
<h1>21. Rotate Socks</h1>
Smelly gear often starts with smelly socks. Invest in plenty of pairs so your teen never wears damp socks twice. Fresh socks mean fresher shoes.

