<h1>1. Host Parent Meetings to Align Expectations</h1>
Let’s be honest—parents, players, and coaches often come into a season with <em>very different</em> ideas about what it’s going to look like.
<pre><strong>Related:</strong>
<a title="20 Questions Every Club Should Answer" href="https://a360f80d.sibforms.com/serve/MUIFAK-x--WLbpqY--3Z8YJBdny3Y51mwSSlwf22l0AhFPCgtgNQb9m2y0iDlkE4hK3u4i8qF2xx3ARUvHr68Jx5V8fihkZKIS-Uky5aALV4eU1h148boN6Vsq4SxgwgLp0NhGH0NkLks1D-gcaXgMVF0KApwxJBpZT_NBZxPiTXBXgQ_HF7TYMJZ1GKetTaa4DcV6Z6t9mpcLHV" target="_blank" rel="noopener">20 Questions Every Club Should Answer</a>
