<h1>2. Follow and watch soccer:</h1>
I’ll admit, maybe I shouldn’t have done this, but back in 2015, when my kids were in elementary school, I picked them up early from school just so we could watch the Champions League final between Man City and Barcelona.

&nbsp;

It wasn’t the most "school-friendly" decision, but seeing their excitement as we watched such a prestigious match together was totally worth it. The energy of the game, the skill on display, and the atmosphere—it was a memory we’ll all treasure.

