Ask any player, and they will tell you that they want to become a better soccer player who has a greater impact on the field. However, those same players will most likely struggle to describe their plan and any concrete action steps for improvement.

&nbsp;

My goal is to change that. I want you to improve your skills and find greater success on and off the pitch.  In this post, I share four tips that will help you improve your soccer skills and take your game to the next level.

&nbsp;
<h3>Step #1 Set Smart Goals</h3>
We all know that setting goals is important, but we often don’t realize how much more important it is to set <strong>Smart Goals</strong>.

&nbsp;

SMART goals stand for <strong>Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, and Time-Bound</strong>.

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Start by picking a specific skill that you want to improve. Do you want every pass you make to go to the right person? Or maybe you want to be able to juggle the ball 50 times without dropping it. </span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Now make smaller goals to track your progress. Try juggling the ball ten times without dropping it. When you can do it consistently, increase that number by five.</span>
