<a href="https://anytime-soccer.com/free-30-day-juggling-training-session/">Free 30-Day Juggling Challenge</a>
</pre>
&nbsp;
<h3>Step #2 Have Fun &amp; Celebrate Your Success</h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s hard to stay motivated if practice feels more like work than it does fun. </span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Set smaller goals and reward yourself after each accomplishment.  Also, come up with games you can play by yourself or with your friends that are both fun and focus on a specific skill. </span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">For example, soccer tag is a great way to have fun while improving your skills.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you need some ideas, check out our e-book Becoming a <a title="" href="https://anytime-soccer.com/become-a-super-rec-coach/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Rec Coach Super Hero</a> for fun games and more.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;
<h3><b>Step #3 Play Against Others In a Low-Pressure Environment</b></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">To improve, you have to practice new skills in a free environment that has low stakes and pressure. This is the best way to experiment and make lots of mistakes.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Also, playing against people with different skill levels challenges you in different ways.   Older players and players with more skill can teach you new moves and force you to move quicker.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Playing with less skilled players gives you more time on the ball and the ability to show leadership.</span>

