&nbsp;

This is a seminal show in the <strong>Inside Scoop</strong> podcast where I, (Neil Crawford, founder of www.anytime-soccer.com) defined the <strong>"Parent-Trainer"</strong> and what role the parent-trainer can play in supporting their child in youth soccer.

&nbsp;

While parent-trainers may differ, most of them share the following in common:

&nbsp;
<ul>
 	<li>Parent-trainers believe in the positive power of deliberate practice.  They have witnessed deliberate practice work well in their life and have seen deliberate practice benefit the lives of other people.</li>
 	<li>Parent-trainers are unwilling to outsource 100% of their child's development (in soccer or anything else) to someone else</li>
 	<li>Parent-trainers are introspective - recognizing the need to strike the right balance needed to support their child in a positive way</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

The majority of soccer parent education does not consider parent-trainers.  This is reasonable, considering how few parent-trainers there are.  However, the Inside Scoop is dedicated to helping parent-trainers navigate the wild world of youth soccer.

